<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-448-487  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 448 487.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Networking Management  Sept 1990 v8 n9 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Researcher apologizes for SAA comments, while users hedge on SAAimplementation.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferrarini, Elizabeth M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A chief research officer of The Gartner Group Inc, Michael Braude,has given apologies to IBM for releasing a press releasecriticizing the company's Systems Application Architecture, anenvironment that offers applications and communicationsconsistency across System/370, AS/400, and PS/2 product lines.andO;Braude wrote that the SAA concept has deteriorated over a periodof three years, from 1987 to 1990.andP;  Research material was used inhis release, although he regrets that the comments were nastierthan he would have liked.andP;  Braude now praises SAA's connectivity,and believes that many of its components are still sound.andO;However, he warns that users should proceed with caution, makingdecisions based on business, not technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gartner Group Inc. (officials and employees)International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Topic:     Research and DevelopmentOperating EnvironmentsPublic relations.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Respondents' SAA outlook: likelyhood of implementation. (graph)Person:    Braude, Michael (attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>